  "body": "Currently if you enable `errors` middleware you get a log for every invalid domain. Which means that if you have multiple search domains every dns request generates a number of error logs. Making `errors` middleware unusable. \r\nExample:\r\n```\r\n03/Mar/2017:14:12:40 +0000 [ERROR 0 test.svc.domain.improbable.io. AAAA] invalid query name\r\n03/Mar/2017:14:12:41 +0000 [ERROR 0 some_other_service.improbable.io.svc.domain.improbable.io. AAAA] invalid query name\r\n03/Mar/2017:14:12:41 +0000 [ERROR 0 some_other_service.improbable.io.domain.improbable.io. AAAA] invalid query name\r\n03/Mar/2017:14:12:41 +0000 [ERROR 0 some_other_service.improbable.io.other_domain.improbable.io. AAAA] 100: Key not found (/skydns/io/something) [881827]\r\n03/Mar/2017:14:12:41 +0000 [ERROR 0 some_other_service.improbable.io.domain.improbable.io. A] no items found\r\n03/Mar/2017:14:12:43 +0000 [ERROR 0 kibana.domain.improbable.io. AAAA] invalid query name\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
